1> Well to fish your gonna need a fishing pole right?<br>
<br>
Lets make a fishing pole<br>
<br>
Step 1 get the resources<br>
a.Fishing-rod requires 7 units of inorganic<br>
b.Fishing-line Guides requires 2 units of metal <br>
c.Fishing-line requires 4 chemical<br>
d.Fishing-rod reel requires 5 units of metal<br>
<br>
Step 2 You will need a generic crafting tool<br>
<br>
Step 3 make sure all the resources are in your main pack and open the tool<br>
<br>
Step 4 go to the generic items <br>
<br>
Step 5 choose fishing pole <br>
<br>
then just follow the steps to create it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Your gonna need some bait for those fish to bite so lets find some fishing bait<br>
<br>
Step 1 find a scout, if you are a scout start foraging<br>
<br>
<br>
These fishing rods need to be loaded to fish so lets load that pole with some bait<br>
<br>
Step 1 Open the radial on the fishing pole.<br>
a. Hold left mouse button down on the fishing pole till radial opens<br>
Step 2 Open<br>
<br>
Step 3 drag the bait into the containter<br>
<br>
You can also just drag and drop the bait onto the rod icon.<br>
<br>
choosing your bait<br>
<br>
you have 3 types of bait that I have found so far<br>
#1 Worm-bait this is foraged<br>
<br>
#2 Bugs-this is foraged<br>
<br>
#3 chum bait-this is what you get from filleting the fish<br>
<br>
<br>
Once baited your going to want some water with some nice weeds or rocks.<br>
This is just my paticular favorite fishing location type, I don't think it really matters.<br>
<br>
Walk out into the water, about knee deep.<br>
<br>
type /fish or make a macro for it. You can also use the radial to cast your fishing line. <br>
<br>
once your bobber is out in the water its time to wait and watch your fishing menu<br>
<br>
The fishing Menu<br>
<br>
Status- Waiting,Nibble,Bite,Caught something<br>
Bait Status-Fresh,Soggy,Mush<br>
Line Range - The furthest I have cast with a rod I made my self was 9.78m<br>
Next Action- Tug up,Tug Right,Tug Left,Small Reel, Stop Fishing<br>
<br>
<br>
Status tells you what is going on with your line and bobber<br>
Bait Status tells you what condition your bait is in.<br>
Line Range shows you how far or close your bobber is to you.<br>
Next Action shows you what you need to click on to preform the next action.<br>
<br>
<br>
you will get nibbles and bites and sometimes they will just steal your bait.<br>
<br>
<br>
I have found that the best time to do one of the rod actions is right after a bite.<br>
<br>
your rod actions are<br>
<br>
tug<br>
tug left<br>
tug right<br>
small reel<br>
stop fishing<br>
<br>
<br>
Once you have your fish you can filet it and get fish meat and more fishing bait from each fish.<br>
<br>
The larger the fish the more meat you get.But it vaires greatly<br>
<br>
above all else have fun and make up good fishing stories.<br>
<br>
SabbathSMC<br>
